post_text: Mrs. Davis is truly the epitome of The RH Way. She dedicates so much time and passion to her scholars and making sure that they can be successful and the best version of themselves in the future. When asked what she hopes for the future for her scholars she stated "My hope is that each and every scholar sets a higher bar of excellence for themselves than any standard outsiders may set for them. I also hope they know to always use their voice to effectively communicate and advocate for what they need." #ResurgenceHall

post_text: Ms. McKinney has really pushed herself and the 2nd-grade team to new heights. The one thing she loves the most about Resurgence Hall is the value the school places on community. "We all work as a team from teachers and staff to the scholars being that no one is left behind." #ResurgenceHall #TogetherWeRise

post_text: Ms. Hill joined our Operations Team this year and has done a phenomenal job serving the Resurgence Hall community. "I love the RH community! The support the families provide not only to scholars but to staff alike is amazing to me. Those partnerships are what makes the school dynamic strong. I look forward to growing at Resurgence!" #OneSchoolOneVision

post_text: Thank you Ms. Packer for all that you do to ensure your scholars succeed in high school, college and life. Ms. Packer said she "loves RHCS because of our strong family partnerships and how supportive families are of their teachers and their child's academic success." It is because families like you and teachers like Ms. Packer, that excellence continues to live at Resurgence Hall. #SpotlightOnStaff
